<Link id="l00008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="8"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\file For Falkor, we want to avoid HW prefetcher instruction tag collisions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that may inhibit the HW prefetching.  This is done in two steps.  Before</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><Highlight kind="comment">/// ISel, we mark strided loads (i.e. those that will likely benefit from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><Highlight kind="comment">/// prefetching) with metadata.  Then, after opcodes have been finalized, we</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><Highlight kind="comment">/// insert MOVs and re-write loads to prevent unintentional tag collisions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// ===---------------------------------------------------------------------===//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
